title._content: 22a. Lieut. Gowllands House afterwards occupied by Dr. Kyngdon who acted as Locum Tenens for Dr. Ward (Not Dated) Dr. R. Ward

description._content: Dr. Kyngdon was the occupant of Lieut. Gowllands house in Martin St. after Gowllands passing in 1874. Dr. Boughton Kyngdon was born in 1819 and travelled between Sydney, Australia and England whilst training and practising as a doctor, eventually settling back in Sydney where he eventually died in 1899. He was married to Elizabeth Cobb and was father to 7 children. Sources: sueyounghistories.com/archives/2009/10/24/boughton-kyngdo...
